License, version 2.1 (LGPL-2.1).

Upstream:   https://github.com/freeswitch/spandsp
Vendored from commit: 797760168945c96e91af55bde9d4edaea2e654f9  (2025-07-07)

What is vendored
----------------
Only the subset needed for V.22 / V.22bis modem support:

  src/native/spandsp/src/
    alloc.c                     complex_vector_int.c    power_meter.c
    async.c                     dds_float.c             tone_detect.c
    bit_operations.c            dds_int.c               v22bis_rx.c
    complex_vector_float.c      logging.c               v22bis_tx.c
                                                        vector_float.c
                                                        vector_int.c

    floating_fudge.h                filter_tools.h
    mmx_sse_decs.h

  src/native/spandsp/src/spandsp/      — SpanDSP public headers
  src/native/spandsp/src/spandsp/private/ — SpanDSP private headers

The T.30, T.38, and fax modules are NOT vendored. The V.27ter, V.29, V.17,
V.32bis, V.34, and V.8 modules are NOT vendored.

Generated files
---------------
The following files were generated at integration time by running SpanDSP's
`make_modem_filter` tool against this commit's source:

  src/native/spandsp/src/v22bis_tx_rrc.h       (from: make_modem_filter -m V.22bis -t)
  src/native/spandsp/src/v22bis_rx_1200_rrc.h  (from: make_modem_filter -m V.22bis1200 -r)
  src/native/spandsp/src/v22bis_rx_2400_rrc.h  (from: make_modem_filter -m V.22bis2400 -r)

These files contain pulse-shaping filter coefficients; they are pure data
and carry the same LGPL-2.1 license as the rest of SpanDSP.

Local modifications
-------------------
The vendored SpanDSP files themselves are unmodified from upstream. A
hand-written configuration file has been added:

  src/native/spandsp/config.h

This file supplies the HAVE_* capability macros that SpanDSP normally gets
from an autotools-generated config.h. It does not modify any SpanDSP code.

